SIMPLE: thenceforth
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thenceforth
<hw>Thence`forth"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>From that
time; thereafter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If the salt have lost his savor, wherewith shall it be salted? it
is <qex>thenceforth</qex> good for nothing.</q> <rj><qau>Matt. v.
13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note> This word is sometimes preceded by <xex>from</xex>, -- a
redundancy sanctioned by custom. <rj><au>Chaucer.</au> <au>John. xix.
12.</au></rj> </note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thenceforward</ent>⟦br⟧
